{{refimprove|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox building | name = Carrousel du Louvre | alternate_names = Le Carrousel | image = | caption = ''[[La Pyramide Inversée]]'', the ''Inverted Pyramid'' skylight, near the entrance to the Louvre | map_type = France Paris | building_type = [[Shopping mall]] | location = [[Paris]], [[France]] |coordinates = {{coord|48.860395|2.337599|display=inline,title}} | inauguration_date = 15 octobre 1993 |floor_area = 10 200 m² |number_of_stores = more than 35 | owner = [[Unibail-Rodamco]] |parking = 615 spaces | website = {{Official website|http://www.carrouseldulouvre.com}} }} The '''Carrousel du Louvre''' is an underground [[shopping mall]] in [[Paris]], [[France]]. The name refers to two nearby sites, the [[Louvre]] museum and the [[Place du Carrousel]]. The mall contains a famous skylight, ''[[La Pyramide Inversée]]'' (the ''Inverted Pyramid''), which plays an important role in the best-selling book ''[[The Da Vinci Code]]''.
==Details== [[File:Plan of the Carrousel du Louvre and the Palais du Louvre 01.svg|thumbnail|left|Plan of the Carrousel du Louvre and the Palais du Louvre]] The shopping mall is located at 99 [[Rue de Rivoli]] in the [[1st arrondissement of Paris|1st arrondissement]]. The mall is located near the [[Tuileries| Tuileries Gardens]], the [[Comédie-Française]], the [[Musée d'Orsay]] and the [[Louvre]]. The nearest metro stop is [[Palais Royal – Musée du Louvre (Paris Métro)|Palais Royal-Musée du Louvre]] (Lines 1 and 7).
The mall covers 10,200 square metres. It was opened in October 1993. Major retail tenants include [[Sephora]], [[Esprit Holdings|Esprit]], the first [[Apple Store]] in France, [[Mariage Frères]] Tea Emporium, [[Plaisirs de Paris]], [[Swarovski]], [[Perigot]], [[Le Tanneur]] and [[Fossil]].
The mall includes a [[food court]], Restaurants du Monde, containing several restaurants including a controversial<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cnn.com/2009/WORLD/europe/10/06/mcdonalds.louvre/ |publisher=CNN | title='Bad taste' cries as McDonald's moves into 'Mona Lisa' museum | accessdate=11 May 2010 | date=7 October 2009}}</ref> [[McDonald's]]. The mall includes a convention centre and exhibition hall.
The shopping mall contains one of a number of entrances to the [[Louvre|Louvre museum]].
On 3 February 2017, the mall was the scene of [[2017 Paris machete attack|an attempted terrorist attack]] by a 29-year-old Egyptian man, in which he slightly injured a soldier before being shot and wounded.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-38863431|title=Louvre attack: Egyptian man, 29, believed to be assailant|date=3 February 2017|accessdate=4 February 2017|publisher=BBC News}}</ref>
