'''Danish Front''' ('''Dansk Front''' in [[Danish language|Danish]]) was an extreme right, [[Nationalism|nationalist]] network in [[Denmark]], whose goal was to ''"keep Denmark for the Danish people"'', thus they were also against [[multiculturalism]] and "alien religions" such as [[Islam]].
The phenomenon known as ''Dansk Front'' consisted of:
* An organization that united many extreme right radicals. * A homepage that consisted of nationalistic messages and [[propaganda]]. The homepage also functioned as an online forum. * A slogan ("Danish Front!") that was used in [[graffiti]], [[t-shirts]], [[stickers]] and such, both for Dansk Front and other extreme right radicals.
Their homepage tried to portray the Danish Front as a new, popular [[Racism|racist]] concept, but many saw them as [[neo-nazis]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}} The leaders of Danish Front discouraged members from using [[swastika]]s and other traditional [[Nazism|nazi]] symbols to express their views.
Members of this organization also used [[violence]] to further their goals.{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}
A number of members of Danish Front had previously been members of [[Dansk Folkeparti]] or [[Dansk Folkepartis Ungdom]] but had been expelled from those political parties.{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}
==Controversial surroundings== * In their yearly review the [[Politiets Efterretningstjeneste|Danish Security Intelligence Service]] (''Politiets Efterretningstjeneste'') found that Danish Front had cooperated with groups such as [[Blood & Honour]] and the English [[Terrorism|terrorist group]] [[Combat 18]].<ref>{{cite web |language=Danish |publisher=Politiets Efterretningstjeneste |url=http://www.pet.dk/upload/pet_%C3%A5rsberetning_03.pdf |year=2003 |title=Politiets Efterretningstjeneste Årsberetning 2003}}</ref> * Danish Front had collaborated with Combat 18 and Blood & Honour, as well as with [[Sweden|Swedish]] radical nationalist groups, and marched with them in [[Salem Municipality|Salem]] during 2005.{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}
== Dissolution == The organization was dissolved on 19 July 2007.
==External links== * [http://www.danskfront.dk Official Homepage] * [http://www.pet.dk/upload/pet_%C3%A5rsberetning_03.pdf The PET yearly review.]
