{{Infobox Magazine | title = Am Féillire | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | editor = | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | frequency = Annually with gaps | circulation = | category = | company = | founded = 1872 | finaldate = 1938 | country = Scotland | based = [[Inverness]] | language = [[Scottish Gaelic language|Scottish Gaelic]] | website = | issn = }}
'''''Am Féillire''''' ({{IPA-gd|əm ˈfeːʎəɾʲə}}) was an annual magazine in [[Scottish Gaelic]] that was first published in 1872 under the name '''''Almanac Gàilig air son 1872''''' in Inverness by J. Noble and ran to 44 pages.<ref name=Union>Ferguson, M., & A. Matheson, ''Scottish Gaelic Union Catalogue'' [[National Library of Scotland]], [[Edinburgh]] 1984.</ref>
It appeared again the following year under the name Am Féillire. Further editions appeared in 1875, 1900 and then annually until 1908 and, following a long gap, finally in 1938. It varied in length, having up to 96 pages.<ref name=Union/>
